name: Hallo Barong
description:
Figure in balinese Mythology, Indonesian culture.

The word "barong" is believed to have arisen from the word bahrwang which can freely be interpreted as a bear. This bear is believed to be a mystical power, a mythical animal that has high magical powers so it is worshiped as a protector.
